radiographic_examinations.findings: Dependent bibasilar atelectasis in lung bases, small hypodensities in the liver dome, spleen, and left kidney, liver is diffusely fatty, spleen slightly enlarged (13.7 cm CC), multiple cystic structures in the head of the pancreas with small punctate calcifications, no evidence of pancreatic inflammation, common bile duct at upper limits of normal (6 mm), no free fluid or air, no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, rectum, sigmoid colon, prostate, and bladder within normal limits, no signs of appendicitis or pelvic/inguinal lymphadenopathy, no suspicious osseous lesions.
